L-Carnitine supplements are best known for accelerating fat loss and improving the muscle mass and bone mass in the body. L-Carnitine is an amino acid found in high concentrations in heart, liver tissues & even in sperms where, inside the cells (mitochondria), L-carnitine helps to transport fat, particularly long-chain fatty acids, into the mitochondria of cells. Once there, the fatty acids can be oxidized—used as fuel—to generate adenosine triphosphate or ATP. L-carnitine does this cellular work both when you exercise and rest. Without adequate carnitine, most dietary fats can't get into the mitochondria and be burned for fuel.
